# EAS Builds

The user runs all `eas build` and `eas submit` commands themselves, in
interactive mode, in their own terminal.

## What I do

- Make code changes, commit them
- Tell the user the exact command to run
- Wait for them to report success / failure / the build URL
- Diagnose failures by fetching logs after the fact (`eas-cli build:list --json`,
  fetching the signed log URLs from the JSON)

## What I do NOT do

- Run `npx eas-cli build ...` or `npx eas-cli submit ...` myself, even with
  `--no-wait`. The user wants full control over what gets queued.
- Pass `--non-interactive`. Interactive mode lets EAS auto-fix credentials
  (provisioning profile regeneration, APNs key setup, etc.) inline.
- Auto-submit to TestFlight / App Store / Play Store. The user submits when
  they decide it's ready.

## Standard build commands the user runs

```bash
cd /Users/munshi/Downloads/endura-v-2/frontend

# iOS production build
npx eas-cli build --platform ios --profile production

# Submit to TestFlight (only when explicitly asked)
npx eas-cli submit --platform ios --latest
```
